JOHANNESBURG - Acting Minister in the Presidency Khumbudzo Ntshavheni is giving an update on government interventions to rebuild the economy and address various issues following the violent protests that took place  in some parts of South Africa. Riots and looting scenes unfolded in KwaZulu-Natal and Gauteng earlier this month, leading to the deaths of over 200 people. WATCH LIVE: Ntshavheni gives update on govt's interventions after unrest  Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.